## Key Features

- **LangGraph Orchestration** - Agents dispatched in parallel via `Send()` API
- **Web Dashboard** - Lit 3 + Vite browser UI with live terminal view (xterm.js)
- **tmux Integration** - Each agent runs in its own pane, attach/detach anytime
- **Git Worktrees** - Isolated workspace per ticket, no branch switching conflicts
- **Knowledge Layer** - SQLite + ChromaDB for decisions, lessons, code patterns
- **Iterative Sprints** - Planning â†’ Development â†’ Review â†’ Loop or Release

## Agents

| Agent | Role | Phase |
|-------|------|-------|
| Product Owner | Requirements analysis, user stories | Planning |
| Architect | Technical design, ticket breakdown | Planning |
| UI Developer | Lit 3 components, browser testing | Development |
| Backend Developer | API routes, services | Development |
| Tester | Test writing and execution | Testing |
| Reviewer | Code review, quality checks | Review |
| Git Agent | Branch management, merging, releases | All |

## Prerequisites

- Python 3.11+
- Node.js 18+
- tmux
- Git 2.30+ with worktree support
- LLM API key (Anthropic or OpenAI)

## Quick Start

```bash
# Clone and install
git clone https://github.com/hannesnortje/AIDevelopment.git
cd AIDevelopment
python -m venv venv && source venv/bin/activate
pip install -e ".[dev]"
cd dashboard && npm install && cd ..

# Configure API keys
export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY="your-key"
# or: export OPENAI_API_KEY="your-key"

# Start the server (opens dashboard at http://localhost:3000)
python -m langgraph_scrum.server --project /path/to/your/project

# Monitor agents in tmux (optional)
tmux attach -t scrum-agents
```

## Configuration

Create `.langgraph/config/server.yaml`:

```yaml
server:
  host: localhost
  port: 8765

llm:
  provider: anthropic
  model: claude-sonnet-4-20250514

agents:
  max_parallel: 5

git:
  auto_push: false
  worktrees_dir: .worktrees
```

